# âš”ï¸ "Sword of Crystalia" Player Handout

Welcome to the continent of Altera. This document outlines the basic knowledge of the world of "Sword of Crystalia" to help you survive as an adventurer.

---

## ğŸ’ 1. World Overview: A World of Mana and Aether

This world is sustained by two mighty forces. Once opposing powers, they are now intricately intertwined, supporting modern civilization.

| Term | Overview | Impact on Players |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Mana** | Life Force itself. The power source of ancient civilizations. | Relates to vitality. If corrupted, it leads to "Voidification," risking transformation into Demons or Undead. |
| **Aether** | Nature/Elemental Power. Divided into Fire, Water, Wind, and Earth. | The source of modern magic (Elemental/Healing Magic). Processed into "Aether Stones" to power tools and daily life. |

---

## ğŸ“œ 2. History: What Era is This?

The current year is A.Y. (Albain Year) **180**. After a long period of turmoil, the new king, **"Adventure King Novem"** (The 9th King), has just ascended to the throne.

### Brief History Timeline

| Era | Overview |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Ancient Dragon Era** | The world was ruled by Dragons and laid to waste. The "Crystalia Empire," wielding Mana technology, achieved God-Slaying (killing the Dragon King Bahamut), releasing Aether into the world. The Empire subsequently perished. |
| **Founding of the Kingdom** | Humans, borrowing wisdom from Elves and Dwarves, founded the "Kingdom of Albain." Civilization flourished through Aether Stone technology and Alchemy. |
| **Modern Chaos** | The previous king, "The Fool King Octo (The 8th)," abandoned his duties, leaving the Kingdom in a de facto state of division. Barbarians and monsters became active across the land. |
| **Current Era (Now)** | The former adventurer, King Novem, has taken the throne. As royal authority is weak, he relies on the "Adventurer's Guild" to deal with global crises. |

> ğŸ‘‰ **Point:** In short, "The government is unreliable, so we need the power of you adventurers!"

---

## ğŸ›¡ï¸ 3. The Adventurer's Guild & Rank System

You belong to the "Adventurer's Guild." In this world, adventurers are "Jacks-of-all-trades" and essential for maintaining local security.

### Adventurer Ranks (Guild Seals)

Seals stamped in your handbook, modeled after "Past Kings," prove your capability.

| Rank | Title | Overview & Role |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **6** | Labyrinth Class | [Starting Point] Novice adventurers. Material gathering, escorting, small-scale barbarian suppression. **Survival rate approx. 60%**. |
| **5** | Sage Class | Proven achievers. Medium-scale suppression and slightly dangerous exploration requests. |
| **4** | Iron Class | Proof of a veteran. Suppression of barbarian settlements, escorting major trade routes. Survival rates increase here. |
| **3** | Temple Class | First-rate elite. Capable of Ancient Dragon subjugation and deep exploration of ancient ruins. |
| **2** | Stone Class | Trusted guild veterans. Coordinators for high-difficulty requests and mentors for rookies. |
| **1** | King Class | The Kingdom's greatest heroes. They undertake special missions from the Guild Master or the Crown. |

---

## ğŸ—ºï¸ 4. Key Locations (Geography)

The Kingdom of Albain is vast, but here are the main areas likely to be stages for your adventure.

### ğŸ° The Central Region: Heart of Civilization

* **Royal Capital Granvalia:** The center of politics and knowledge. Home to the Magic Academy and Royal Library, though corruption festers beneath the nobility.
* **Commercial City Argas:** A logistics hub where anything can be found. A lively city ruled by the Merchant Guild.
* **City of Vice, Weiss:** A city of art and gambling. The nightlife is the best in the Kingdom, but the shadows of the underworld are deep.

### ğŸŒ² The Western Frontier: Frontline of Adventure

* **Labyrinth City Dungeon Tower:** Headquarters of the Adventurer's Guild. Home to the living "Windlas Labyrinth," bustling with adventurers seeking fortune.
* **Elmwood Great Forest:** A vast forest inhabited by Elves. The source of Aether; entry without permission is forbidden.

### ğŸ”ï¸ The Northern Frontier: Wall of Frost

* **Fortress City Phalanx:** The northern bulwark stopping barbarian invasions (Giants, etc.). A military city concentrating Dwarven technology.
* **Hot Spring Town Thermia:** A healing spa town for wounded soldiers and adventurers.

### ğŸŒŠ The East & South: Sea and Sand

* **Maritime City San Marina:** A trade city with tropical breezes. Cultural exchange with Mermen is active.
* **Solis Desert:** A barren land bearing the scars of the Ancient War. Only Lizardfolk caravans traverse here.

---

## ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ¤â€ğŸ§‘ 5. Races & Relationships

Many races coexist with humans in this world.

* **Humans:** The central race of the Kingdom. Skilled at integrating knowledge, though individual differences are vast.
* **Elves:** Dwellers of the Western Great Forest. Originators of magic. They keep a distance from humans but maintain technical exchange.
* **Dwarves:** Dwellers of the Northern Mountains. Master smiths. Stubborn artisans who insist, "Magic metal cannot be processed without Dragon's breath."
* **Lizardfolk:** Descendants of the Ancient Empire. Some blend into human society as farmers or boatmen, while others uphold traditions in deserts and swamps.
* **Mermen:** People of the Sea. Friendly trade partners in the South, but difficult and proud in the East; personality varies by region.

---

## âš—ï¸ 6. Useful Technology for Adventure

* **Potions:** Healing medicine created through Alchemy. They do not last long, so local procurement or crafting skills are vital for long journeys.
* **Aether Stones:** Batteries for magic tools. They power lamps, heaters, and simple magical weaponry.
* **Artifacts:** "Lost Technology" excavated from dungeons and ruins. They possess powerful abilities that modern technology cannot reproduce.

Are you ready? Grab your Adventurer's Handbook and step into a new era of exploration!
